This paper is about using deep reinforcement learning to create a self-sustaining Central Pattern Generator (CPG) network for rhythmic motion. The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and Structured Control Nets (SCNs) in this context. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
